{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"arid-stump-twin","description":"## Why\n\nThe epic's end state is exactly TWO real LLM workflows (plan-review, completion-verification) on\nthe engine plus the ONE retained visual-editing sample — with the throwaway scaffolding removed so\nonly what earns its keep remains.\n\n## What\n\nRemove the throwaway sample workflows per Joe's selection: `src/rebar/llm/workflow/examples/\ncode_review.yaml` and the `templates.py` scaffold (used by `rebar workflow new`). Preserve\nforwarding shims / public API for anything still referenced (e.g. keep `rebar workflow new` working\nvia a minimal inline scaffold or a documented replacement). KEEP epic A's\n`examples/review_skeleton.yaml` as the visual-editing refinement sample. Confirm the final\ninventory and that the gates run on the two real workflows.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Delete `examples/code_review.yaml` + `templates.py`; update/replace any references\n  (`rebar workflow new`, tests, docs) with a preserved shim or documented path.\n- Verify end state: two real workflows (plan-review, completion-verification) + the retained\n  `review_skeleton.yaml` sample; no orphaned references.\n- Depends on B5 (cutover complete, so the bespoke samples are truly unused).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `examples/code_review.yaml` and `templates.py` are removed; any still-referenced surface\n      (e.g. `rebar workflow new`) keeps working via a preserved shim or documented replacement.\n- [ ] `examples/review_skeleton.yaml` is retained as the visual-editing sample; no orphaned\n      references to the removed files remain (grep-clean).\n- [ ] End state confirmed: exactly two real LLM workflows (plan-review, completion-verification) +\n      the one retained sample.\n- [ ] `make lint` + the full test suite pass.","id":"7e48-b675-c8ac-4c2c","parent_id":"72d5-79ec-9e2e-4a2b","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"B6: Remove throwaway sample workflows; confirm two-real-workflow end state"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782422799226754001,"uuid":"666cf046-df6c-457f-a964-658f14363031"}